bibdata.title: Updated template files do not load in development

comments.body:
Closing this issue and quoting the comment from https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/pull/1135#issuecomment-802401119 `In the checkin we said to remove the tmpl files and keep only the .rb files. After looking into this I rejected it as an option. I'm quoting my note from slack I kept solid only the holding_library.tmpl file so that we don’t need to generate it every time. I rejected the idea of using the .rb files that we generate through the #generate method because they are being generated by retrieving data from the tables. With that said every time you start lando and you generate the .rb files using the tables from the database the tables would be empty and the generated .rb files would be empty. Unless you also call the alma api every time you start lando so that you populate the tables. We don’t want to call the alma api every time we run the app in development or test. So it is better to keep the tmpl files and use them through the #generate_from_templates method so that we will create the .rb files locally in case they don’t exist.
Also this Pr addresses the removal of the double label in the orangelight display and updates the Location::Holdings table in bibdata. It also improves the code by removing unused lines of code and the generation of a nil file.`

Delete https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/blob/590c0712fe4b04114c69ce9998c7e7238ebfb858/app/services/location_maps_generator_service.rb#L50 and make the copy force overwrite.

This will solve developer problems having mysterious test failures which 75% of the time are due to out of data translation maps.
closed by #1161

lib_jobs.title: Ensure that the custom Mudd Library Container Profiles map to the existing ASpace Container Profiles

comments.body:
Currently, the following mapping exists between ASpace Container Profile names and AbID shelving size codes:

```ruby
{
      'Objects' => 'C',

      'BoxQ' => 'L',
      'Double Elephant size box' => 'Z',
      'Double Elephant volume' => 'D',
      'Elephant size box' => 'P',
      'Elephant volume' => 'E',
      'Folio' => 'F',

      'Mudd OS depth' => 'DO',
      'Mudd OS height' => 'H',
      'Mudd OS length' => 'LO',
      'Mudd ST records center' => 'S',
      'Mudd ST manuscript' => 'S',
      'Mudd ST half-manuscript' => 'S',
      'Mudd ST other' => 'S',
      'Mudd OS open' => 'O',

      'NBox' => 'B',
      'Ordinary' => 'N',
      'Quarto' => 'Q',
      'Small' => 'S'
    }
```
(please see https://github.com/pulibrary/lib_jobs/blob/absolute-ids/app/models/absolute_id.rb#L35)

Please note that there is some duplication amongst these: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1lpZFv6uVOM1BFIrDl48wAY-3XwXnKTFR/edit#gid=831808871
The real enhancement here is to ensure that redundant/identical AbID prefixes are mapped to different ASpace Container Profiles where needed.
